Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you donâ€™t have symptoms.

We encourage British nationals in Fiji to register their details with the British High Commission. If you are a UK/EU national seeking to leave Fiji to return home please send us your details by emailing SuvaCS@fco.gov.uk with the following information for all passengers:
Full name as it appears on passport
passport number
nationality
date of birth
current location
telephone numbers if you have one
intended destination
In registering your details, you will receive regular information about the situation in Fiji, including if any further flights become available.
On 26 March, Nadi Airport will close to all scheduled flights. We will continue to publish guidance on our social media on what people should do if they believe this leaves them stranded. Check our Facebook page and our Twitter feed.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
